snippet: Clint Dempsey had a goal and assist in the first half to give Seattle the lead, but Juninho’s tiebreaking road goal early in the second half sent the Los Angeles Galaxy to the Major League Soccer Cup final for the ninth time in franchise history...
abstract: Los Angeles Galaxy and Seattle Sounders draw, 2-2, in Western Conference final but Galaxy wins on aggregate to advance to MLS Cup final for ninth time in franchise history; other soccer news noted.
lead_paragraph: Clint Dempsey had a goal and assist in the first half to give Seattle the lead, but Juninho’s tiebreaking road goal early in the second half sent the Los Angeles Galaxy to the Major League Soccer Cup final for the ninth time in franchise history after their Western Conference final with the Seattle Sounders ended 2-2 on aggregate.

headline.main: Galaxy Advance to M.L.S. Cup Final
